      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i know u aren't a doctor but u seem to know a lot about it. it just feels like the warfarin is doing more harm than good with all the side effects and the stress of the testing. if i started doing the smoothies every morning and taking like 4000mg of garlic a day would that be enough to keep my blood thin enough so i dont get a clot? i just want a way to do this without the doctor constantly breathing down my neck.",
